"```sql\nSELECT P.ID, P.Admission\nFROM Patient P\nJOIN Laboratory L ON P.ID = L.ID\nWHERE P.SEX = 'F'\n  AND (YEAR(CURRENT_DATE) - YEAR(P.Birthday)) >= 50\n  AND (L.RBC <= 3.5 OR L.RBC >= 6.0);\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects the patient ID and admission status for female patients aged 50 and above who have an abnormal red blood cell count. It joins the `Patient` and `Laboratory` tables on the patient ID and applies the necessary conditions based on the provided evidence."